'''Scurrius, the Rat King''' is a [[boss]] residing in the [[Varrock Sewers]]. As a mid-level boss meant for players with a combat level of 60-90, Scurrius is meant to introduce various mechanics that are present in higher-level play, such as switching [[protection prayers]] quickly during combat as well as dodging attacks and managing multiple monsters mid-fight.

Scurrius can be fought in either the public room or in an [[instance]]. It has two distinct stats if the player is fighting it in the public or an instanced room; the public variant of Scurrius is stronger than the instanced version, and has many more [[Hitpoints]]. [[Ironmen]] can participate with other accounts and will receive killcount, although they will not receive any drops except medium clues if they can manage to attain MVP. [[Group Ironman Mode|Group Ironmen]] have access to a shared instance allowing them to fight Scurrius together.

Scurrius rewards a substantially greater amount of combat experience than normal, especially with [[rat bone weapons]], giving competitive amounts of experience compared to [[Nightmare Zone]] and [[sand crab]]s, though high-levelled players will still be better off training combat through existing methods. 

Although the boss drops [[rat meat]], this meat cannot be cooked during the fight since players cannot light fires in its lair; attempting to do so produces the message, "It's far too damp for you to light a fire here."

[[Dwarf multicannon|Cannons]] cannot be set up in Scurrius's lair. Attempting to do so produces the message, "It's far too damp for you to set up a cannon in here."

