==Trivia ==
* A {{WP|rat king}} is a collection of rats whose tails are intertwined and bound together in some way. Much like a real life rat king, the tails of the mage head and range head seem to be intertwined with the main tail as well.
*The examine text refers to the myth that rats are always present in urban areas, even if the person doesn't see them.
* Scurrius was originally conceived as a concept from the [[April 2023 Game Jam#The_Rat_King_(Free-to-play_mechanics-based_boss)|April 2023 Game Jam]].
* Unlike most large monsters, Scurrius drops its loot on the centre of the 3x3 tiles it occupies, rather than its south-westernmost tile. [[Long bone]]s,  [[curved bone]]s, and [[Clue scroll (medium)|medium clues]] are dropped on the south-westernmost tile, however.
* It was hinted at during the 26 January 2024 Old School Live stream that one of the smaller rats is actually in control of Scurrius, presumably the mage head is in control of Scurrius itself.

